# CLAUDE.md.example -- The Logicist (Template)

This file documents the expected structure of the `CLAUDE.md` that belongs in this directory.
The actual `CLAUDE.md` is excluded from version control (see `../NOTICE.md`).

## Purpose

The Logicist is the second agent in the pipeline. It translates research evidence into
mathematically rigorous TLA+ specifications, verifies them through exhaustive model
checking (TLC), and produces verified contracts that the downstream agents must follow.

## Expected CLAUDE.md Sections

1. Identity and Context (position in pipeline, relationship to other agents)
2. Dual-Directory Model (agent infra in lab/, specs in validium/specs/ or zkl2/specs/)
3. Research Unit Structure (0-input/, 1-formalization/v0-analysis/, v1-fix/)
4. Operational Principles (first-principles formalism, mathematical rigor, adversary within)
5. The Five-Phase Verification Pipeline
6. TLA+ Specification Standards (canonical structure, naming, commenting)
7. Tooling (unit generator, TLA+ runner)
8. Git Workflow and Documentation Standards
9. Behavioral Constraints

## Expected Skills (.claude/commands/)

| Skill | Phase | Purpose |
|-------|-------|---------|
| `/1-formalize` | Phase 1 | Convert research into verified TLA+ specification |
| `/2-audit` | Phase 2 | Verify formalization faithfully represents the source |
| `/3-diagnose` | Phase 3 | Analyze verification failure, propose protocol fix |
| `/4-fix` | Phase 4 | Implement fix, re-verify all invariants |
| `/5-review` | Phase 5 | Final critical design review before handoff |
| `/status` | -- | Quick status check |
| `/resume` | -- | Resume work on existing unit |
